In the Matter of the General Assignment of William L. Earll to H. Melville Renaud and Elmer E. Dey, Jr., for the Benefit of Creditors. C. Milton Foreman, Appellant, v. H. Melville Renaud, Elmer E. Dey, Jr., as Assignees, etc., of William L. Earll, and Morse & Buffum, Respondents.

Motion for reargument denied, with ten dollars costs. Motion for leave to appeal to the Court of Appeals denied. Present — Lazansky, P. J., Hagarty, Carswell, Adel and Close, JJ.
